{{Quote|Make me a Great River...a stream to carry the endangered, the wounded, the weary to safety.|[[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke Skywalker]], quoted by [[Han Solo/Legends|Han Solo]]|<ref name="The New Jedi Order: Edge of Victory II: Rebirth">''[[The New Jedi Order: Edge of Victory II: Rebirth]]''</ref>}}
The '''Great River''' was an [[Jedi Underground|underground]] fugitive network created by [[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke Skywalker]] during the war with the [[Yuuzhan Vong]]. It was created to protect the [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] not only from the Yuuzhan Vong, but from those who would attempt to betray the Jedi to appease the Vong, such as the [[Peace Brigade]].

In its early existence, the Great River network was a series of hidden routes and strongholds where Jedi and their allies could meet and take refuge from the persecuting Yuuzhan Vong fleets. Important locales for the River included [[Shelter]], a space station owned by [[Lando Calrissian/Legends|Lando Calrissian]] in the heart of [[Maw Cluster/Legends|the Maw]], and [[Eclipse Station]], an uncharted planet in the [[Deep Core/Legends|Deep Core]] that temporarily housed the leading members of the [[New Jedi Order]].

Involved in the Great River were a number of rescue fliers, such as [[Uldir Lochett]] and his crew. Working nominally under the [[New Republic/Legends|New Republic]] Search and Rescue Corps, in reality they took their order from Master Skywalker himself.

